name: Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley
intro:
Whether you’re in it to Zin it, or just need a Riesling to run, Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley is the ultimate California weekend running adventure. Starting in the heart of San Francisco, teams of 12 (or 6), will run relay-style while experiencing the best parts of Northern California. The 200-ish mile course brings runners over the Golden Gate Bridge, through Sausalito’s charming downtown, next to endless rows of grapevines and past world-famous wineries. 

 

Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley 2017 will be going into a lottery. Sign up for the Wait List to be the first to find out when it will open! 


GREAT NEWS! All 2016 Reebok Ragnar Relay captains will be receiving free Reebok One Series running shoes!! As a captain, we know you are committed to going the distance and Reebok wants your feedback. Check out our Reebok Shoes page for more info!

Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley is part of the Double Medal Series. Run both Reebok Ragnar So Cal and Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley and earn the Ragnar Republic Double Medal.

2016 Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley Charity Team Opportunities

At Ragnar, we believe in miles. We believe the first mile, the last mile, and every mile in between teach us something about our teammates, our humanity and ourselves. Most importantly, we believe in going the extra mile. The Ragnar Extra Mile Program is inspired by generosity and compassion in an effort to help those that need it the most.

We are sorry you weren't selected for the Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley race, but fear not! Rest assured, there are still some alternatives for you to secure your team registration for this year.  We have partnered with several local charities in San Francisco and Sonoma County, as well as a few great charities around the nation.  Through this commitment to fundraise we will extend a limited number of teams for each charity, so act fast!  We will continue to update this page as the charity spots fill up so keep an eye out for weekly changes to this page.  We promise you, these spots won't last long so act fast and reach out to one of our amazing charities for more details.

Here's what to do!

  1. Team Captains only will reach out to their preferred charity’s contact directly (see list of charities below).  Do not reach out to Ragnar.  All initial contact requests must go through the charity.

  2. The charity contact will than respond to your inquiry with a minimum fundraising commitment and additional details of your next steps to secure your charity team.

  3. Each team will be required to create a fundraising page for the charity of their choice.  Charities will provide details of how to do this and what fundraising platforms they prefer.

  4. While teams are starting their fundraising the charities will secure a spot with us and we will then provide the captains with a Registration URL, Password and team specific Registration Code.

  5. Once the above steps are completed teams will work closely with each charity and Ragnar to help maximize their fundraising efforts.  Don't worry, you won't be on your own.  You will be part of an amazing group of runners that will help bring a charitable impact to Northern California like only Ragnarians can do!

Details vary from charity to charity so please reach out to the contact information listed in the description directly.  Through your fundraising efforts for one of the amazing charities listed below, you too can go the extra mile and be part of an amazing race this year!

 

Primary Charity for Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley 2016:

Lazarex Cancer Foundation

Team for Life is the endurance fundraising program of Lazarex Cancer Foundation. People from all of life's’ crossroads join Team for Life to compete in premier endurance events while doing their part to give back to those in dire medical need, by raising money to help advanced stage cancer patients. Lazarex Cancer Foundation is the only organization of its type in the United States that is removing the financial burden of the advanced stage cancer patients whose only hope for staying alive is through a clinical trial. LCF pays for gas, travel, lodging, car rentals, and diagnostics so that a patient can afford to participate and take advantage of medical breakthroughs in a clinical trial setting. LCF also provides financial assistance to a patient for travel with a companion so they not alone during their treatment. Furthermore, if a patient needs assistance in finding a clinical trial, an LCF patient navigator will assist the patient in researching the options available to the patient. We prosper in the belief that the size of a patient’s checkbook should not stand between them and the choices they make or the treatment they need to keep fighting against cancer. To learn more about Team for Life and the Lazarex Cancer Foundation go HERE.

Secondary Charities for Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley 2016:

Larkin Street Youth Services

Larkin Street provides youth between the ages of 12 and 24 with the help they need to rebuild their lives.  Each year, more than 3,000 youth walk through our doors seeking help.  We give them a place where they can feel safe; rebuild their sense of self-respect, trust, and hope; learn school, life and job skills; and find the confidence to build a future.

Larkin Street was founded in 1984 by a group of local business owners, church members, and neighbors who were concerned by the rising number of young people engaging in risky behaviors on the streets of San Francisco.  With comprehensive youth service programs located throughout San Francisco, Larkin Street Youth Services I now an internationally recognized model successfully integrating housing, education, employment and health services to get homeless and at-risk kids off the street.  To learn more about how Larkin Street Youth Services helps make a better tomorrow for the youth of today go HERE.

Girls on the Run - Sonoma County

We believe that every girl can embrace who she is, can define who she wants to be, can rise to any challenge, can change the world.  Can.  Our mission is to inspire girls to be joyful, healthy and confident using a fun, experience-based curriculum which creatively integrates running.  We envision a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams.

Girls on the Run honors its core values.  We strive to recognize our power and responsibility to be intentional in our decision making, embrace our differences and find strength in our connectedness.  We strive to express joy, optimism and gratitude through our words, thoughts and actions.  Nurturing our physical, emotional and spiritual health while leading with an open heart and assuming positive intent we stand up for ourselves and others.  To learn more about Girls on the Run go HERE.

Back on My Feet

Back on My Feet combats homelessness through the power of running, community support, and essential employment and housing resources. We believe in the philosophy similar to Ragnar that “there is magic when we come together and accomplish something we could never do alone." At Back on My Feet we see this every Monday, Wednesday and Friday at 5:45am when volunteers from the community come together with individuals experiencing homelessness to run side by side and support each other mile by mile.

If you and 11 of your friends, family, co-workers or strangers seek to together conquer 200 miles - this race is for you. Your also have the chance to make this race even more meaningful and FundRace for Back on My Feet.

The benefits are great but most importantly you will be making a difference in the lives of individuals experiencing homelessness. With every $1 you raise it returns nearly $2.50 to the local community through increased economic output from employment and reduction in costs for shelter, medical services, incarceration, and drug and alcohol treatment. Back on My Feet proves that there is hope, that individuals can achieve things they never thought possible, and that there are people who will support them along the way. Be one of those people and join us in the fight against homelessness by running Ragnar for Back on My Feet.

St. Jude Children's Research Hospital

St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital is leading the way the world understands, treats and defeats childhood cancer and other deadly diseases. St. Jude has the world’s best survival rates for the most aggressive childhood cancer, and treatments invented at St. Jude have helped push the overall childhood cancer survival rate from 20 percent to 80 percent since we opened more than 50 years ago. St. Jude Heroes are an exclusive group of dedicated athletes committed to raising funds for the lifesaving mission of St. Jude Children's Research Hospital. As a St. Jude Hero, you'll receive fundraising tools and support, along with event-specific benefits. More importantly, you'll help kids diagnosed with cancer and other life-threatening diseases. Families never receive a bill from St. Jude for treatment, travel, housing or food — because all a family should worry about is helping their child live. To learn more about becoming an official St. Jude Heroes fundraising team, please click HERE.

Stupid Cancer

Stupid Cancer, a 501(c)3 nonprofit organization, is the largest charity that comprehensively addresses young adult cancer through advocacy, research, support, outreach, awareness, mobile health and social media.  Our innovative, award-winning and evidence-based programs and services serve as a global bullhorn to propel the young adult cancer movement forward.

Young adult cancer (age15-39) is largely unknown in the war on cancer with 72,000 new diagnoses each year.  That’s one every eight minutes.  That is not OK!  This neglected group-now millions strong-has limited resources, inadequate support, and, more importantly, a lack of awareness and understanding from the community around them. reg_system.name: Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley
reg_system.description: Whether you’re in it to Zin it, or just need a Riesling to run, Reebok Ragnar Napa Valley is the ultimate California weekend running adventure. Starting in the heart of San Francisco, teams of 12 (or 6), will run relay-style while experiencing the best parts of Northern California. The 200-ish mile course brings runners over the Golden Gate Bridge, through Sausalito’s charming downtown, next to endless rows of grapevines and past world-famous wineries. Because we only have 300 spots available, Ragnar will host a lottery from April 7 to May 5. Here’s how it will work.• To enter, Team Captains will pay a $25 refundable application fee (If you don’t get in this money will be refunded. If you do get in, the $25 will be applied to your team entry).• On May 12th, if you are accepted into the lottery your credit card will be charged automatically with the full amount of the team ($1,740 for Regular teams and $1,140 for Ultra teams).• All teams will be contacted by May 12th about their race acceptance.
